# Strategy docs stay local — competitive posture, not operational doctrine.
docs/strategy/

# docs/ops/RUNBOOK.md is intentionally public (operator-transparency doctrine —
# the runbook is the procedural half of what /.well-known/motebit-transparency.json
# declares; see docs/doctrine/operator-transparency.md). docs/ops/SECRETS.md is
# the secrets-topology inventory — no actual values, but documents the
# single-point-of-compromise surface for the relay. That belongs locked down.
docs/ops/SECRETS.md
.npmrc

# Patent filings (confidential, never public)
patents/
PATENT-BLUEPRINT.md

# Service runtime artifacts (identity keys, local SQLite). Generated on
# first `pnpm dev` boot per service. Contains private keys — never commit.
services/*/data/

